`currentUser` is a variable of type `User`, so you can only use its (and its parents&#39;) method through it.

You could cast the actual instance to a `Student` and store it in a temporary variable of that type to use `Student`&#39;s methods:

```java
Student currentStudent = (Student) currentUser;
currentStudent.someStudentMethod();
```

Of course, you can also omit the storing and call the method directly on the cast instance:
```java
((Student) currentUser).someStudentMethod();
```

